    "statistics": {
      "abilities": [
        {
          "ability_type": "offensive",
          "action_type": {
            "name": "One Action",
            "subtype": "action_type",
            "type": "stat_block_section"
          },
          "activation_name": "Contact Ally",
          "effect": "You cast *message* at 1st rank to a target that you know is also wearing a *lion\u2019s pelt* uniform. If you and the target share an insignia, the spell is heightened to 3rd rank.",
          "frequency": "once per hour",
          "links": [
            {
              "alt": "message",
              "aonid": 1598,
              "game-obj": "Spells",
              "name": "message",
              "type": "link"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Activate",
          "subtype": "activation",
          "traits": [
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 11,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "6a30ff50ed821ab5b9699b2f3d68c0d6",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Arcane",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 452",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 452",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 452,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "This magic comes from the arcane tradition, which is built on logic and rationality. Anything with this trait is magical.  \n  \nA creature with this trait is primarily constituted of or has a strong connection to arcane magic.",
              "type": "trait"
            },
            {
              "alternate_link": {
                "alternate_type": "legacy",
                "aonid": 32,
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "type": "alternate_link"
              },
              "edition": "remastered",
              "game-id": "e32d877417a40fe977d27634dc14f99f",
              "game-obj": "Traits",
              "name": "Concentrate",
              "sources": [
                {
                  "errata": {
                    "alt": "2.0",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "2.0",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "link": {
                    "alt": "Player Core pg. 454",
                    "aonid": 216,
                    "game-obj": "Sources",
                    "name": "Player Core pg. 454",
                    "type": "link"
                  },
                  "name": "Player Core",
                  "page": 454,
                  "type": "source"
                }
              ],
              "text": "An action with this trait requires a degree of mental concentration and discipline.",
              "type": "trait"
            }
          ],
          "type": "stat_block_section"
        }
      ],
      "access": {
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Lion Blades",
            "aonid": 22,
            "game-obj": "Archetypes",
            "name": "Lion Blades",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "subtype": "access",
        "text": "You\u2019re a member of the Lion Blades.",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      },
      "subtype": "statistics",
      "type": "stat_block_section",
      "usage": {
        "subtype": "usage",
        "text": "worn armor",
        "type": "stat_block_section"
      }
    },
    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "Laurisa Tromaine ordered these as prototype uniforms. The fur-lined pauldrons bear the insignia of a lion with a blade in its mouth. The type of blade indicates which bard school one graduated from. When you disguise the armor via its *raiment* rune, you can choose whether to conceal this symbol or not. You can also use the rune\u2019s activation to quickly display or hide the insignia.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 98,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "invest",
            "aonid": 2799,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "invest",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Invested",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 219,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
